        <p data-uuid="832f14900f4b46f0b6667e7fb14e665d">In cities of the late 1800s and early 1900s, there was a shortage of affordable housing. This forced many poor families to squeeze into tiny tenement apartments, which were frequently unsafe and unsanitary. Journalist and photographer <b><dfn title="Riis, Jacob">Jacob Riis</dfn></b> became famous for exposing the horrible conditions in New York City tenements.<br />
        </p>
        <section class="historical-source nobg" data-uuid="500678ab57c44bca8c22e1005b9d28d1">
